          <h2>What Is an Extended Car Warranty?</h2>
          
          <p>An extended car warranty (technically called a <strong>vehicle service contract</strong>) provides coverage for mechanical breakdowns after your manufacturer's warranty expires. Unlike traditional insurance, these contracts cover specific vehicle components and systems—protecting you from unexpected repair bills that can reach thousands of dollars.</p>

